<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1337,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249">
Crown yellowish (
<figureCitation box="[406,483,1445,1470]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 16" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1361,1384]" captionTargetBox="[160,1430,199,1322]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,195,1338]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 16 Alebroides chiasmaticus Yu &amp; Yang, sp. nov., 14 whole body, dorsal view 15 face 16 head and thorax, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230417/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="249">
Fig 
<number box="[452,483,1446,1470]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
). Coronal suture brownish, not reaching apex of crown (
<figureCitation box="[1116,1193,1445,1470]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 16" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1361,1384]" captionTargetBox="[160,1430,199,1322]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,195,1338]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 16 Alebroides chiasmaticus Yu &amp; Yang, sp. nov., 14 whole body, dorsal view 15 face 16 head and thorax, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230417/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="249">
Fig 
<number box="[1162,1193,1446,1470]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
). Face yellowish (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 16" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1361,1384]" captionTargetBox="[160,1430,199,1322]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,195,1338]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 16 Alebroides chiasmaticus Yu &amp; Yang, sp. nov., 14 whole body, dorsal view 15 face 16 head and thorax, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230417/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="249">
Fig 
<number box="[151,182,1481,1506]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
). Pronotum semitransparent posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[645,723,1481,1506]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 16" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1361,1384]" captionTargetBox="[160,1430,199,1322]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,195,1338]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 16 Alebroides chiasmaticus Yu &amp; Yang, sp. nov., 14 whole body, dorsal view 15 face 16 head and thorax, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230417/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="249">
Fig 
<number box="[692,723,1482,1506]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
). Scutellum yellowish except apically dark (
<figureCitation box="[1228,1307,1481,1506]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 16" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1361,1384]" captionTargetBox="[160,1430,199,1322]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,195,1338]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 16 Alebroides chiasmaticus Yu &amp; Yang, sp. nov., 14 whole body, dorsal view 15 face 16 head and thorax, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230417/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="249">
Fig 
<number box="[1276,1307,1482,1506]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
). Forewing hoary, semitransparent; hindwing hyaline (
<figureCitation box="[629,706,1517,1542]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 16" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1361,1384]" captionTargetBox="[160,1430,199,1322]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,195,1338]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 16 Alebroides chiasmaticus Yu &amp; Yang, sp. nov., 14 whole body, dorsal view 15 face 16 head and thorax, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230417/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="249">
Fig 
<number box="[675,706,1518,1542]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
). Abdomen yellowish. Legs hoary except claws brownish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1337,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249">
Male ventral abdominal apodemes not reaching third segment. Male pygofer triangular, apical margin with setae; ventral pygofer appendage distinctly exceeding pygofer, thick, straight, pubescent, apex acuminate; dorsal bridge less than 
<number box="[335,346,1626,1650]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[357,371,1626,1650]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249" value="3.0">3</number>
length of pygofer, lateral lobes poorly developed (
<figureCitation box="[943,1116,1625,1650]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 25" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1566,1589]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,1542]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,195,1542]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 25 Alebroides chiasmaticus Yu &amp; Yang, sp. nov., 17 male terminalia, lateral view 18 male pygofer, dorsal view 19 male pygofer, lateral view 20 subgenital plate, ventral view 21 paramere 22 aedeagus, ventral view 23 aedeagus, lateral view 24 anal tube process, lateral view 25 connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230418/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="249">
Figs 
<number box="[1000,1073,1626,1650]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249" value="17.18">17, 18</number>
, 
<number box="[1085,1116,1626,1650]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plates tapering, with 
<number box="[214,228,1662,1686]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249" value="2.0">2</number>
rows of 
<number box="[346,374,1662,1686]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249" value="21.0">21</number>
macrosetae, 
<number box="[534,548,1662,1686]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249" value="3.0">3</number>
rows of ca. 
<number box="[697,726,1661,1686]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249" value="45.0">45</number>
feeble microsetae, ca. 
<number box="[995,1023,1662,1686]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249" value="18.0">18</number>
marginal setae and 
<number box="[1272,1286,1661,1686]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249" value="6.0">6</number>
basal group macrosetae (
<figureCitation box="[291,369,1697,1722]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 25" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1566,1589]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,1542]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,195,1542]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 25 Alebroides chiasmaticus Yu &amp; Yang, sp. nov., 17 male terminalia, lateral view 18 male pygofer, dorsal view 19 male pygofer, lateral view 20 subgenital plate, ventral view 21 paramere 22 aedeagus, ventral view 23 aedeagus, lateral view 24 anal tube process, lateral view 25 connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230418/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="249">
Fig 
<number box="[337,369,1698,1722]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
). Paramere elongate, apex falcate, subapex with setae, with slight swelling 
<number box="[1210,1222,1698,1722]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number box="[1231,1245,1698,1722]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249" value="4.0">4</number>
of distance from base (
<figureCitation box="[216,295,1733,1758]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 25" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1566,1589]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,1542]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,195,1542]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 25 Alebroides chiasmaticus Yu &amp; Yang, sp. nov., 17 male terminalia, lateral view 18 male pygofer, dorsal view 19 male pygofer, lateral view 20 subgenital plate, ventral view 21 paramere 22 aedeagus, ventral view 23 aedeagus, lateral view 24 anal tube process, lateral view 25 connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230418/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="249">
Fig 
<number box="[264,295,1734,1758]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249" value="21.0">21</number>
</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus expanded from base to 
<number box="[701,715,1734,1758]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[724,736,1734,1758]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249" value="3.0">3</number>
length in ventral view, distal 
<number box="[1075,1086,1734,1758]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1097,1111,1734,1758]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249" value="3.0">3</number>
abruptly narrower, with two long crossed falcate processes arising from preatrium (
<figureCitation box="[769,901,1769,1794]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 25" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1566,1589]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,1542]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,195,1542]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 25 Alebroides chiasmaticus Yu &amp; Yang, sp. nov., 17 male terminalia, lateral view 18 male pygofer, dorsal view 19 male pygofer, lateral view 20 subgenital plate, ventral view 21 paramere 22 aedeagus, ventral view 23 aedeagus, lateral view 24 anal tube process, lateral view 25 connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230418/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="249">
Figs 
<number box="[826,901,1770,1794]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249" value="22.23">22, 23</number>
</figureCitation>
). Anal tube process elongate, apex branched as in fig 
<number box="[218,250,1806,1830]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249" value="24.0">24</number>
. Connective lamellate, approximately as long as wide, without distinct posterior emargination (
<figureCitation box="[1316,1393,1805,1830]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 25" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1566,1589]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,1542]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,195,1542]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 25 Alebroides chiasmaticus Yu &amp; Yang, sp. nov., 17 male terminalia, lateral view 18 male pygofer, dorsal view 19 male pygofer, lateral view 20 subgenital plate, ventral view 21 paramere 22 aedeagus, ventral view 23 aedeagus, lateral view 24 anal tube process, lateral view 25 connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230418/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="249">
Fig 
<number box="[1362,1393,1805,1830]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="249" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1337,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1841,1866]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species name alludes to aedeagal process crossed in ventral view, the Latin word “ 
<taxonomicName box="[161,310,1877,1902]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Alebroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="249" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chiasmaticus">chiasmaticus</taxonomicName>
” means crossed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="249" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1337,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1913,1938]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new speices is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Thapa" authorityName="Thapa" box="[685,859,1913,1938]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Alebroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="249" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sohii">
<emphasis box="[685,702,1914,1937]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="249">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[720,774,1913,1937]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="249">sohii</emphasis>
Thapa
</taxonomicName>
, but differs in having the aedeagal basal process branched, sinuate in lateral view and crossed in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[864,998,1949,1974]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 25" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1566,1589]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,1542]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,195,1542]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 25 Alebroides chiasmaticus Yu &amp; Yang, sp. nov., 17 male terminalia, lateral view 18 male pygofer, dorsal view 19 male pygofer, lateral view 20 subgenital plate, ventral view 21 paramere 22 aedeagus, ventral view 23 aedeagus, lateral view 24 anal tube process, lateral view 25 connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230418/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="249">
Figs 
<number box="[923,998,1950,1974]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249" value="22.23">22, 23</number>
</figureCitation>
), the shaft unexpanded in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[158,233,1985,2010]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 25" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1566,1589]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,1542]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,195,1542]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 25 Alebroides chiasmaticus Yu &amp; Yang, sp. nov., 17 male terminalia, lateral view 18 male pygofer, dorsal view 19 male pygofer, lateral view 20 subgenital plate, ventral view 21 paramere 22 aedeagus, ventral view 23 aedeagus, lateral view 24 anal tube process, lateral view 25 connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230418/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="249">
Fig 
<number box="[204,233,1986,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
) and the male pygofer appendage pubescent (
<figureCitation box="[746,876,1985,2010]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 25" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1566,1589]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,1542]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,195,1542]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 25 Alebroides chiasmaticus Yu &amp; Yang, sp. nov., 17 male terminalia, lateral view 18 male pygofer, dorsal view 19 male pygofer, lateral view 20 subgenital plate, ventral view 21 paramere 22 aedeagus, ventral view 23 aedeagus, lateral view 24 anal tube process, lateral view 25 connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230418/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="249">
Figs 
<number box="[803,876,1986,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="249" value="18.19">18, 19</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
